<dl id="s14013cv"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us14" href="#s14013cv">Oxen of the Sun: </a><a href="../../ff/unbs/s14all.htm#s14013cv">sector 13(cv)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> that you ere were there</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">When you are entered the <font color="green">[Dutch]</font> house the first thing you encounter is a looking-glass. No question but a true emblem of polite hospitality; for though it reflects yourself in your own figure, &apos;tis yet no longer than while you are there before it. When you are gone once, it flatters the next comer, without the least remembrance <mark>that you ere were there</mark>. <small> William Peacock, <a name="WPEP" href="/udra/udex.htm#wpep"><cite title="source">English Prose from Mandeville to Ruskin</cite></a> (1903), 77, Felltham</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
